Fixed a bug that caused the WaitHelper::TIMEOUT to be 0 when WAIT_TIMEOUT is not set.

The line

sets TIMEOUT to 0 if the WAIT_TIMEOUT is not set because nil.to_i is evaluated to 0 and the 240 is never assigned.

Merge pull request #109 from dhemery/fixdelete

Confirm deletion: Don't call unimplemented methods

Confirm deletion: Don't call unimplemented methods

If the table view's data source does not implement
tableView:commitEditingStyle:forRowAtIndexPath:,
then the data source does not support deletion.
So return without deleting.

The table view's delegate need not implement
tableView:didEndEditingRowAtIndexPath:, so check before
sending the message.
